## IV. PROPOSED PHASE 17 STRATEGY

### Priority 1 — AUT Extreme Bleed Stress Test (IDX-006 hardening)
Add a dedicated unit test with position [(-5.0, 5.0)](file:///c:/Users/zephy/Documents/Brinkmanship/brinkmanship_engine/src/main.rs#91-126) and zero factions/estates to isolate pure rubber band bleed with no generation interference. Validate that AUT drains to 0 within ~20 ticks.

### Priority 2 — UI Surface: The Matrix Comes Alive
Wire the following to the React frontend:
- `position_history` → IdeologyCompass breadcrumb trail (last 10 positions as fading dots)
- [position](file:///c:/Users/zephy/Documents/Brinkmanship/brinkmanship_engine/src/scenario.rs#232-248) vs `perceived_position` → Show gap as "Deep State Delta" overlay on the compass
- [flavor_label](file:///c:/Users/zephy/Documents/Brinkmanship/brinkmanship_engine/src/ideology_matrix.rs#98-123) vs `perceived_flavor_label` → Show dual-label in the HUD header
- Velocity Shock action_log entries → Flash a `⚡ POLITICAL SHOCK` banner in the UI

### Priority 3 — Persian Gulf Crisis Scenario File
Write `scenarios/persian_gulf_crisis.json` using the new [ScenarioDef](file:///c:/Users/zephy/Documents/Brinkmanship/brinkmanship_engine/src/scenario.rs#35-52) format. This will be the engine's first officially supported scenario and serve as the regression file for all future balance testing.

### Priority 4 — IDX-014: Zone Gate Consequences (Emerging)
The zone gates (`FiveYearPlan`, `BureaucraticFamine`, `CapitalFlight`, etc.) are detected but produce no mechanical consequences. Phase 17 should wire [check_zone_gates()](file:///c:/Users/zephy/Documents/Brinkmanship/brinkmanship_engine/src/ideology_matrix.rs#170-209) into the chronos tick loop to deliver per-tick bonuses and disaster triggers based on active gates.

---

## V. ARCHITECT'S SELF-ASSESSMENT

Phase 16 was more complex than anticipated due to Rust ownership semantics in the journey test harness (borrow-after-move requiring `.clone()`) and physics boundary conditions that required careful reasoning (shock detection, decaying volatility). All issues were resolved cleanly with no compromises to the simulation logic. The engine is now more realistic, more constrained, and more testable than at any point in its history.

**The simulation has gravity. The matrix has teeth. Phase 17 will give it a face.**

